node.text: I coached @nastialiukin on @dancingabc so it only made sense that she coached me for the Olympics. This video just makes me  laugh. I love this memory. My admiration and respect for Olympic athletes is over flowing. The dedication and sacrifices they endure to be The Best is inspiring. Each year pushing the limits and their abilities to the edge. I feel very fortunate to have had the opportunity to meet and work with  Gold Medalist Olympians who we perceive to be super human. And as impressive as their skills are, getting to know them as human beings was a gift. #olympics

Daily Rituals:Just like an Athlete needs a coach to help them reach their full potential in sport, I often listen to powerful speakers who motivate and coach me in life. Sometimes I listen to the same thing over and over again until I truly feel the words wash over me, giving me clarity and energy to tackle whatever lies ahead. 
This clip of @thelesbrown always gets me fired up. When all feels lost just remember “ITS NOT OVER UNTIL I WIN”

node.text:
Old footage of me playing Ren McCormack in FOOTLOOSE on the West End in London. 
My first big role, skinny little inexperienced kid giving his All 8 Times a week. My jeans 👖 were soaking wet after every show. I would ring them out and put the damp jeans back on for the second show on Friday’s and Saturday’s. 
I would lose my voice all the time cause I didn’t know how to use it properly. Took me a few months to understand breathe control and proper support. That experience taught me so much including a work ethic that I carry with me into everything I do today. Also, shout out to my boy @giovannispanoofficial #worldtheatreday

node.text: I coached @nastialiukin on @dancingabc so it only made sense that she coached me for the Olympics. This video just makes me  laugh. I love this memory. My admiration and respect for Olympic athletes is over flowing. The dedication and sacrifices they endure to be The Best is inspiring. Each year pushing the limits and their abilities to the edge. I feel very fortunate to have had the opportunity to meet and work with  Gold Medalist Olympians who we perceive to be super human. And as impressive as their skills are, getting to know them as human beings was a gift. #olympics

node.text:
A few years ago my Mom told me that my spirit animal was a Giraffe. Huh? I was a little surprised. I was expecting a Tiger, Lion, Bear, Eagle or something fierce and strong like that. Funny how we perceive ourselves. I asked my mom why she thought I was a Giraffe 🦒 and she replied 
.
“ Giraffes can see far into the future, they have the ability to reach things that are unreachable to others, they have the ability to remain above the fray . 
.
Giraffes help us explain the expression “to stick ones neck out”. When we take risks by going further than we ever imagined possible, you see worlds of possibilities. 
. 
The Giraffes vulnerability when lowering its head to drink is a reminder to us that if we lose sight of our greater vision and consciousness and sink into a mundane way of life, we risk losing our spiritual connection. 
.
The Giraffes strong body represents being grounded in physical existence and its ability to see symbolizes spiritual vision” 
.

.

.
.

WOW! An absolute honor to be nominated for 2 Emmy awards. Last year my goal was to try and bring a little bit of joy, entertainment and creativity to everyone. It makes it even more special having danced with my talented and beautiful woman @hayley.erbert for 2-3 of the nominated pieces. 
As always it takes a village to bring these pieces to life. From music, costume, lighting,  scheduling, set design etc. Thank you to everyone who was involved. #emmys
